We can examine the differential peaks using a heatmap

vsd = vst(dds, blind = FALSE) # first transform the data
df <- as.data.frame(colData(dds)[,c("Condition", "age", "SampleID", "Batch")], stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
## Warning in as.data.frame(colData(dds)[, c("Condition", "age", "SampleID", :
## Arguments in '...' ignored
rownames(df) = paste0(df$SampleID, "_", df$age)
df =as.data.frame(colData(dds)[,c("mutation", "age", "Condition")],stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
## Warning in as.data.frame(colData(dds)[, c("mutation", "age",
## "Condition")], : Arguments in '...' ignored
count.matrix <- removeBatchEffect(assay(vsd), batch = colData(dds)$mutation, design = model.matrix( ~ colData(dds)$Condition))

# generate Z-scores from counts
Means.vsd = rowMeans(count.matrix)
SD.vsd = rowSds(count.matrix)
norm.vsd = (count.matrix-Means.vsd) / SD.vsd
colnames(norm.vsd) = rownames(df)
norm.vsd = norm.vsd[,order(sapply(strsplit(colnames(norm.vsd), "_"), "[", 4))]
res = results(dds, contrast = c("Condition", "Old", "Young")) #  specify fold change order Old/Young
select_005 = order(res$padj)[1:length(which(res$padj < 0.05))]
length(select_005)
## [1] 629
# number of sign diff peaks = 2859
x = norm.vsd[select_005,]
clusters = pam(x, 2) # use pam clustering here to obtain consistent clusters, you can choose the cluster number 
x = x[names(sort(clusters$clustering)), ]

df_ordered <-df[with(df, order(age)), ]
proper_order<-rownames(df_ordered)
x_ordered<-x[ ,proper_order]

ph<-pheatmap(x_ordered, cluster_rows = FALSE,
         cluster_cols = F,
         show_rownames=F,
         show_colnames = T,
         annotation_col=df)

We can examine the peaks using a PCA plot

cct = assay(vsd, blind  = T)
pvars <- rowVars(cct)
select <- order(pvars, decreasing = TRUE)[seq_len(min(500, length(pvars)))] #  select top 500 peaks
PCA <- prcomp(t(cct)[, select], scale = F)
percentVar <- round(100 * PCA$sdev ^ 2/ sum(PCA$sdev ^ 2), 1)
plotPCA.df = data.frame(PC1 = PCA$x[,1], PC2 = PCA$x[,2], PC3 = PCA$x[,3], PC4 = PCA$x[,4], sample = paste0(colData(dds)$SampleID,"_", colData(dds)$age), condition = as.character(colData(dds)$age), batch = colData(dds)$mutation)

qplot(PC1, PC2, data = plotPCA.df,color = as.factor(dds$Condition), main = "PC1 vs PC2 top 500 peaks", size = I(6))+ labs(x = paste0("PC1, VarExp:", round(percentVar[1],4)),  y = paste0("PC2, VarExp:", round(percentVar[2],4))) + scale_color_manual(values = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(n = 5, name = "RdBu"))(4))+ theme_classic() + theme(aspect.ratio=1)

qplot(PC1, PC2, data = plotPCA.df,color = as.factor(dds$mutation), main = "PC1 vs PC2 top 500 peaks", size = I(6))+ labs(x = paste0("PC1, VarExp:", round(percentVar[1],4)),  y = paste0("PC2, VarExp:", round(percentVar[2],4))) + scale_color_manual(values = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(n = 5, name = "RdBu"))(4))+ theme_classic() + theme(aspect.ratio=1)
